content: Does the site have printed articles from trusted sources that support Kamala which we can use to engage online community members?

Hello <@1276944224985550960> sharing printed handouts of talking points is a fantastic idea. We have loads of material from trusted sources that you can printout and pass along to folks. You can find this in the Reach app library where you can use the Search function to get content for specific topics.

I hope this is a correct thread to post this.  I just saw a great thread here called "supporter content"  I assume that is for us to share on social media correct? I would like to share some that are in that thread on twitter.  How do I share it right from Discord to twitter?  Thanks.  (also if I have to go to the Reach app to share it, how would I find this content & also Reach app always freezes on my phone so it's hard to use).
<#1250876565366243348> is a preview of what will be added next day into Reach.

ohhhh. ok. thanks. how do i find the specific ones that are shown in that thread on reach? just look in general? and is reach only an app or can it be accessed on a laptop browser? if so, can you provide the link.

You can sign into [Reach](https://app.reach.vote/) with a web browser.  [Content made by volunteers](https://app.reach.vote/library/gallery/c07cfbbe-ed31-4770-8303-833364ba39b8?campaign=democrats) is the gallery where <#1250876565366243348> feeds.
Thank you very much! Got in on my browser & you sent me right to that section!
